addRegistryEntry(address).details: Adds address as valid registry entry into the Registry Must be callable only by allowed factory contract

applyParamChange(address).details: Gives ParamChange contract temporary permission to apply its parameter changes into EthernalDb Only address of valid ParamChange contract can be passed Permission must be taken back right after applying the change

construct(address).details: Constructor for this contract. Native constructor is not used, because we use a forwarder pointing to single instance of this contract, therefore constructor must be called explicitly.

params._db: Address of EternalDb related to this registry

isEmergency().details: Returns whether emergency stop is happening

isFactory(address).details: Returns whether address is valid registry entry factory

isRegistryEntry(address).details: Returns whether address is valid registry entry
isRegistryEntry(address).return: True if address is registry entry

setEmergency(bool).details: Sets emergency state to pause all trading operations Must be callable only by authenticated user

setFactory(address,bool).details: Sets whether address is factory allowed to add registry entries into registry Must be callable only by authenticated user

params._isFactory: Whether the address is allowed factory
